data.text_e:
Once there were three girls as beautiful as gold, who bragged about the rare antiques each of them possessed;

“I have a flowered head scarf,” the first said to the others— “embroidered with cross stitches by my own grandmother.”

“I have a jeweled needle”—the second proudly stated—
“from my great grandmother with small diamonds decorated.”

Only the third girl laughed silently with pride, And quietly opened the door to an alcove inside;

“The dearest small antique of all, is mine alone, right here— my great grandmother herself of more than a hundred years!”
